1227
01:58:25,534 --> 01:58:37,991
[SPEAKER_54]: Colleagues, today I rise to adjourn in memory of Mark Salzberg, a noted progressive activist, neighborhood leader, and beloved member of the Westside and Venice community, who passed away on June 27th after a long illness.

1228
01:58:40,053 --> 01:58:43,818
[SPEAKER_54]: Mark dedicated his life to civic engagement and local democracy.

1229
01:58:44,660 --> 01:58:51,088
[SPEAKER_54]: Mark was a leader in the democratic community and a founding member of the West Los Angeles Democrats in 2004,

1230
01:58:51,305 --> 01:58:58,011
[SPEAKER_54]: where he served as president and became a trusted advisor to elected officials at every level, local, county, state, and federal.

1231
01:58:58,792 --> 01:59:02,255
[SPEAKER_54]: A pillar of the club, Mark also founded its Environment and Clean Energy Committee.

1232
01:59:03,416 --> 01:59:19,590
[SPEAKER_54]: Long before climate change was at the center of political debate, he was pushing Democrats to prioritize clean energy and environmental stewardship, bringing in expert speakers, advancing resolutions, and ensuring that the future of the planet was part of every conversation.

1233
01:59:20,600 --> 01:59:23,706
[SPEAKER_54]: His civic imagination extended to cultural projects.

1234
01:59:23,726 --> 01:59:36,110
[SPEAKER_54]: Mark supported efforts to create a Venice Museum and a historic trolley car, advocated for a Pacific electric heritage display near the Centennial Library, and even mediated proposals for new attractions at Venice Beach.

1235
01:59:37,112 --> 01:59:43,063
[SPEAKER_54]: A graduate of Carleton College, Mark built a career in technology as a project manager, bringing products to market.

1236
01:59:43,516 --> 01:59:53,647
[SPEAKER_54]: But it was his passion for civic life, for bringing neighbors together, strengthening democracy, and preserving this city's unique culture that defined his public service.

1237
01:59:54,668 --> 02:00:04,859
[SPEAKER_54]: Today, we are honored to be joined in council chambers by Mark's wife, Nancy, and by Kara Robin of the West LA Democratic Club, representing the community that Mark helped build and sustain.

1238
02:00:04,899 --> 02:00:09,945
[SPEAKER_54]: On behalf of the Los Angeles City Council, I extend our heartfelt condolences to Nancy.

1239
02:00:10,280 --> 02:00:13,604
[SPEAKER_54]: to Jenny and Alex, to the Salzburg family, and to all who mourn.

1240
02:00:14,465 --> 02:00:21,434
[SPEAKER_54]: In recognition of his many contributions to our city, I respectfully ask that the Los Angeles City Council adjourn today's meeting in memory of Mark Salzburg.

1241
02:00:22,215 --> 02:00:28,182
[SPEAKER_54]: May his memory be a blessing, and may his legacy of progressive advocacy and community leadership continue to inspire us all.

1242
02:00:29,043 --> 02:00:29,424
[SPEAKER_54]: Thank you.

1243
02:00:30,385 --> 02:00:32,187
[SPEAKER_41]: Thank you so much, Council Member Yaroslavsky.

1244
